{{Use dmy dates|date=February 2016}} {{Use British English|date=February 2016}} {{Infobox cricketer | name = Boltwood | image = | country = England | fullname = unknown | nickname = | birth_date = c.1755 | birth_place = [[England]] | batting = unknown hand | bowling = underarm: unknown hand and type | role = batsman | club1 = unknown | year1 = c.1775–1785 | club2 = | year2 = | date = 20 March | year = 2013 | columns = 0 | source = [[G. B. Buckley]] }}
'''Boltwood''' (first name and dates unknown) was an English [[first-class cricket|first-class]] [[cricket]]er who made a single known appearance for [[All-England cricket teams|All-England]] against [[Chertsey Cricket Club|Chertsey]] at [[Laleham Burway]] on 10–11 September 1778.<ref name=GB86>Buckley, p.86.</ref><ref name="CA45">{{cite web|url=https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Scorecards/0/45.html |publisher=''CricketArchive'' |title=Chertsey v All-England 1778 |accessdate=20 March 2013}}</ref> Boltwood scored 34 runs with a highest score of 27.<ref name="CA45"/> Boltwood may have played in the return match at the [[Artillery Ground]] on 15 September, but no details of that match have survived.<ref name=GB86/>
As Boltwood had established his reputation by 1778, he must have been active for some years previously. Very few players were mentioned by name in contemporary reports and there are no other references to Boltwood.
