{{Infobox Minor League Baseball |name = Dominican Summer League Cubs |founded = |city = Boca Chica |misc = |logo = |uniformlogo = |class level = Rookie |past class level= |current league = [[Dominican Summer League]] |conference = |division = Boca Chica North |past league = |majorleague = [[Chicago Cubs]] |pastmajorleague = |nickname = Cubs |pastnames = |ballpark = Baseball City Complex |pastparks = |leaguenum = 0 |leaguechamps = None |divnum = 0 |divisionchamps = |owner = Chicago Cubs |manager = Juan Cabrera |gm = }}
The '''Dominican Summer League Cubs''' or '''DSL Cubs''' are a [[Rookie League|rookie league]] affiliate of the [[Chicago Cubs]] based in the [[Dominican Republic]].<ref>[http://web.minorleaguebaseball.com/milb/stats/stats.jsp?t=t_ros&cid=602 MinorLeagueBaseball.com]</ref> They play in the Boca Chica North Division of the [[Dominican Summer League]].
==History== The team began in 1991 with a joint affiliation with the [[Kansas City Royals]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.baseball-reference.com/minors/team.cgi?id%3D6a176e10 |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2014-03-14 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140313063028/http://www.baseball-reference.com/minors/team.cgi?id=6a176e10 |archivedate=2014-03-13 |df= }}</ref> An affiliation with the [[Colorado Rockies]] was added in 1992.<ref>https://www.baseball-reference.com/minors/team.cgi?id=117816d0</ref>
For the 1993 season, the team shared an affiliation with the [[Texas Rangers (baseball)|Texas Rangers]].<ref>https://www.baseball-reference.com/minors/team.cgi?id=0e88765e</ref> They then shared an affiliation with the [[San Diego Padres]] for the next three seasons (1994–1996).<ref>https://www.baseball-reference.com/minors/team.cgi?id=c0ecc38c</ref>
The team became independently affiliated with the Cubs in 1997. From 2008 to 2012, the team split into two squads as DSL Cubs 1 and DSL Cubs 2, but became a unified team again for the 2013 season.<ref>https://www.baseball-reference.com/minors/league.cgi?code=DOSL&class=FRk</ref>
