{{Use dmy dates|date=August 2015}} {{Use British English|date=August 2015}} {{Infobox cricket ground | ground_name = Ideal Clothiers Ground | nickname = | country = England | image = | location = [[Wellingborough]], [[Northamptonshire]] | establishment = 1929 <small>(first recorded match)</small> | seating_capacity = | end1 = | end2 = | year1 = 1929 | club1 = [[Northamptonshire County Cricket Club|Northamptonshire]] | date = 1 September | year = 2010 | source = https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Grounds/11/2227.html Ground profile }}
'''Ideal Clothiers Ground''' was a [[cricket]] ground in [[Wellingborough]], [[Northamptonshire]]. The ground was constructed by Ideal Clothiers, a clothes making company based in Wellingborough. The first and only [[first-class cricket|first-class]] match on the ground was in 1929, when [[Northamptonshire County Cricket Club|Northamptonshire]] played [[Oxford University Cricket Club|Oxford University]].<ref>[https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Grounds/11/2227_f.html First-Class Matches played on Ideal Clothiers Ground]</ref>
The ground fell out of use in the 1970s.
