{{Infobox football biography | name = Okeem Challenger | image = | fullname = Okeem Challenger | height = {{height|m=1.78|precision=0}} | birth_date = {{birth date and age|1989|08|22|df=yes}} | birth_place =[[Antigua and Barbuda]] | currentclub = [[SAP F.C.|SAP]] | clubnumber = | position = [[Forward (association football)|Striker]] | youthyears1= | youthclubs1= | years1= 2004– | clubs1= [[SAP F.C.|SAP]] | caps1= | goals1 = | nationalyears1= 2008– | nationalteam1= [[Antigua and Barbuda national football team|Antigua and Barbuda]] | nationalcaps1= 5 | nationalgoals1 = 2 | pcupdate = 10:01, 24 May 2008 (UTC) | ntupdate = 29 December 2008 }}
'''Okeem Challenger''' (born 22 August 1989) is an [[Antigua and Barbuda|Antiguan and Barbudan]] [[association football|footballer]] who plays for [[SAP F.C.|SAP]] in the [[Antigua and Barbuda Premier Division]].
==International career== Nicknamed ''Soda'', Challenger made his debut for [[Antigua and Barbuda national football team|Antigua and Barbuda]] in a March 2008 [[FIFA World Cup qualification]] match against [[Aruba national football team|Aruba]], in which game he came on as a late substitute for Randolph Burton and immediately scored the winner. He has earned five caps since, but only played in one World Cup qualification game.<ref>[https://www.fifa.com/worldfootball/statisticsandrecords/players/player=296036/index.html Record at FIFA Tournaments] - FIFA</ref>
