[[Image:Paraguaybasket.png|110px|right|Paraguayan Basketball Federation Logo]]

The '''Paraguayan Basketball Federation''' (in [[Spanish language|Spanish]]: ''Confederación Paraguaya de Básquetbol'') is the governing body of [[basketball]] in [[Paraguay]]. The PBF organizes both the [[Paraguayan National Basketball League|National League]] (for teams outside of [[Asunción]]) and the [[Paraguayan Metropolitan Basketball League|Metropolitan League]] (only for teams from Asunción), and runs the [[Paraguay national basketball team]].

==History==
In 1936, no governing body of basketball existed in Paraguay, so basketball was part of the ''Paraguayan Sports Association'' until 1947, the year in which the Paraguayan Basketball Federation was founded. That same year, it joined the [[International Basketball Federation]] (FIBA).

