{{Infobox cricket ground | ground_name = St George's Road | nickname = | country = England | image = Millom cricket ground and Holborn Hill, Black Combe behind - geograph.org.uk - 540588.jpg | location = [[Millom]], [[Cumberland]] | coord = {{coord|54.2101|-3.2741|display=inline}} | establishment = {{circa|1925}} | seating_capacity = | end1 = | end2 = | year1 = 1961&ndash;2002 | club1 = [[Cumberland County Cricket Club|Cumberland]] | date = 19 August | year = 2010 | source = https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Grounds/11/634.html Ground profile }}
'''St George's Road''' is a [[cricket]] ground located off St George's Road in [[Millom]], [[Cumberland]]. The ground is bordered to the south–east by the [[Cumbrian Coast Line]] and to the north and west by housing. It is the home venue of Millom Cricket Club.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://millomcc.play-cricket.com/home/home.asp|title=Millom Cricket Club|publisher=www.millomcc.play-cricket.com|accessdate=14 February 2013}}</ref>
==History== Constructed prior to 1925, the first recorded match on the ground saw Cumberland{{#tag:ref|This was an informal Cumberland team, with present [[Cumberland County Cricket Club]] not formed until 1948.|group=n}} play a [[North Lancashire and Cumbria League|North Lancashire League]] team in 1925.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Grounds/11/634_misc.html|title=Other matches played on St George's Road, Millom|publisher=CricketArchive|accessdate=14 February 2013}}</ref> [[Cumberland County Cricket Club|Cumberland]] first played at the ground the 1961 [[Minor Counties Championship]] against the [[Lancashire County Cricket Club|Lancashire Second XI]].<ref name="MCM">{{cite web|url=https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Grounds/11/634_minc.html|title=Minor Counties Championship Matches played on St George's Road, Millom|publisher=CricketArchive|accessdate=14 February 2013}}</ref> The county played four further Minor Counties Championship matches there in the 1960s, before a single match annually there between 1971 and 1994, with the exception of 1977, when no match was played there.<ref name="MCM"/> Cumberland played four further Minor Counties Championship matches there, the last of which saw them play [[Suffolk County Cricket Club|Suffolk]] in 2000. Cumberland have played a total of 32 Minor Counties Championship at the ground to date.<ref name="MCM"/> In 2001, the ground hosted its only [[List A cricket|List A]] match when Cumberland played the [[Warwickshire Cricket Board]] in the [[2002 Cheltenham & Gloucester Trophy]],{{#tag:ref|Early rounds were played in 2001 to avoid fixture congestion in 2002.|group=n}}<ref>{{cite web|url=https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Grounds/11/634_a.html|title=List A Matches played on St George's Road, Millom|publisher=CricketArchive|accessdate=14 February 2013}}</ref> which the Warwickshire Cricket Board won by 17 runs, thanks largely to [[Jim Troughton]]'s 115 runs and four wickets.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Scorecards/72/72858.html|title=Cumberland v Warwickshire Cricket Board, 2002 Cheltenham & Gloucester Trophy|publisher=CricketArchive|accessdate=14 February 2013}}</ref> The following season, the ground hosted a single [[MCCA Knockout Trophy]] between Cumberland and the [[Yorkshire Cricket Board]], however the match was abandoned without a ball bowled.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Grounds/11/634_mint.html|title=Minor Counties Trophy Matches played on St George's Road, Millom|publisher=CricketArchive|accessdate=14 February 2013}}</ref>
