{{Infobox venue | name = Çarşamba Yeşilırmak Stadium | nickname = | native_name = Çarşamba Yeşilırmak Stadyumu | native_name_lang = | fullname = | former names = | logo_image = | logo_caption = | image = | image_size = | image_alt = | caption = | pushpin_map = Turkey | pushpin_mapsize = | pushpin_map_caption = Location of the stadium in Turkey. | pushpin_label_position = | address = Çarşamba Sugar Refinery, Beyyenice,Çarşamba | location = [[Çarşamba]], [[Samsun Province|Samsun]], Turkey | coordinates = {{coord|41|10|29|N|36|42|37|E|type:landmark|display=inline,title}} | type = | genre = | broke_ground = | built = | opened = {{start date and age|2013|03|07}} | renovated = | expanded = | closed = | demolished = | owner = | operator = | surface = | scoreboard = | production = | cost = | architect = | builder = | project_manager = | structural engineer = | services engineer = | general_contractor = | main_contractors = | seating_type = | capacity = 5,000 | suites = | record_attendance = | dimensions = | field_shape = | acreage = | volume = | tenants = [[2017 Summer Deaflympics]] | embedded = | website = <!-- {{URL|example.com}} --> | publictransit = }}
'''Çarşamba Yeşilırmak Stadium''', also known as the '''New City Stadium of Çarşamba''', ({{lang-tr|Çarşamba Yeşilırmak Stadyumu}} or ''Çarşamba Yeni Şehir Stadyumu'') is a football stadium located in [[Çarşamba]] district of [[Samsun Province]], northern Turkey. It was named after the [[Yeşilırmak (river)|Yeşilırmak River]], which flows just east of the venue. It is the home ground of the local football team Çarşambaspor, who play in the [[Turkish Regional Amateur League|Regional Amateur Leahue]].<ref name="cb2"/>
The stadium is situated at Çarşamba Sugar Refinery, Beyyenice,Çarşamba. It was built by the Municipality of Çarşamba on a land of {{convert|40|daa|acre|abbr=on}} in exchange for the real estate of the 1952-built and demolished old city stadium. Its opening took place on March 7, 2013 although not fully completed.<ref name="he1"/> It has a nine-lane track for athletics competitions.<ref name="ys1"/> The stadium's seating capacity is 5,000.<ref name="cb1"/>
==International events hosted== The venue will host football events of the [[2017 Summer Deaflympics]].<ref name="d"/>
